north chagrin reservation of the metropark system.

 

i just mapquested the area. 

 

what you're looking for is the sr 91 exit off of interstate 90.  it's the first exit east of the 271 split. [or last, if you're coming from east of 271.]

 

interestingly enough, you turn left when get off, no matter which direction you were coming from, which will head you south.

 

the first major intersection [as i recall, it was the first one with a traffic light] you turn left onto chardon road.

- - - - -

coming from the south, i suppose you would already *be* on sr91 or ir271, so when you get to chardon road, you turn right.  i *think* there *might* be a chardon road exit off of ir271, but i wouldn't bet the farm on it.  mapquest is a leetle vague on this one.  an interchange shows up at the 100mi. magnification, but not at street level.  so, if worse comes to worst, you can always swing up and onto ir90 east, and then just get off at the first exit.

- - - - -

once you're on chardon road, heading east from the intersection of chardon and sr91, you go *past* the *first* [flashing] traffic signal, which is only for the fire department, and you turn right at the *second* traffic light, which may be identified as buttermilk falls parkway.

 

go down the hill, and the parking lot, shelter house and cookstoves are immediately on your right.

 

can't say that i've got the v-ball net any more, though...  cougar was keeper, at last count.  i might still have his addy around, somewhere.  i'll have to look.
